In the context of increasing efforts to decarbonize supply chains, emerging economies are at risk of being left behind due to a lack of green infrastructure. How can emerging economies harness frontier technologies to support supply chain de-carbonization and ensure sustainable movement of goods? World Insight with Tian Wei brings you a panel at this year's World Economic Forum - Decarbonizing Supply Chains: Leaving No One Behind. Joining us: Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala Director-General, World Trade Organization  Helen Mountford Chief Executive Officer, ClimateWorks Foundation  Jacques Vandermeiren Chief Executive Officer, Port of Antwerp-Bruges  Jose Alejandro Rojas Pardini Minister of Private Investments, Ministry of the Presidency of Panama  Niclas MÃ¥rtensson Chief Executive Officer, Stena Line AB